01:06:15,599 --> 01:06:17,427
I hope you all heard.

792
01:06:17,505 --> 01:06:19,805
None of the three who tried it escaped.

793
01:06:20,404 --> 01:06:22,122
Here, nobody gets away.

794
01:06:23,505 --> 01:06:26,829
This isn't a showplace like
Saint-Claire's was, is it?

795
01:06:27,903 --> 01:06:30,005
Go ahead and complain if you want.

796
01:06:30,208 --> 01:06:32,020
Course, nobody will listen.

797
01:06:32,309 --> 01:06:35,926
You can be as happy as
you like, it's your right.

798
01:06:36,403 --> 01:06:37,809
Your only right.

799
01:07:51,399 --> 01:07:53,425
Should I shut them up for you, boss?

800
01:07:54,107 --> 01:07:55,213
No.

801
01:07:55,916 --> 01:07:58,220
Don't you like music?

802
01:08:11,699 --> 01:08:13,613
What brings you two here?

803
01:08:13,707 --> 01:08:15,112
That man leading the singing,

804
01:08:15,163 --> 01:08:17,207
didn't he belong to Pierre Saint-Claire?

805
01:08:31,595 --> 01:08:33,490
I gotta have tea.
- Sambo, shut them up

806
01:08:33,541 --> 01:08:35,416
and bed them down for the night.

807
01:08:35,467 --> 01:08:37,017
Right, boss.
- Go ahead.

808
01:08:37,603 --> 01:08:39,314
He could cause trouble you know.

809
01:08:47,910 --> 01:08:49,521
He's always caused some trouble,

810
01:08:49,572 --> 01:08:51,121
but what can he do out here?

811
01:08:51,191 --> 01:08:53,423
I like the singing, it's pleasant.
Sit down.

812
01:08:53,511 --> 01:08:55,011
What if he escapes?

813
01:08:55,089 --> 01:08:57,511
Nobody's gotten away
from here alive yet.

814
01:08:57,999 --> 01:09:00,116
John here hasn't been that lucky.

815
01:09:00,167 --> 01:09:02,030
Last night, 15 got away.

816
01:09:02,081 --> 01:09:03,237
And right before picking time!

817
01:09:03,288 --> 01:09:05,304
Don't you have dogs and guards?

818
01:09:05,355 --> 01:09:06,358
Sure.

819
01:09:06,409 --> 01:09:07,749
We got back four of them.

820
01:09:07,812 --> 01:09:08,727
And the rest?

821
01:09:08,778 --> 01:09:10,905
They're hiding in the monastery.

822
01:09:11,601 --> 01:09:14,046
About time we burned a
couple of their sheds again.

823
01:09:14,097 --> 01:09:15,530
Seems they need another lesson.

824
01:09:15,581 --> 01:09:17,911
The situation since then
has changed considerable.

825
01:09:17,962 --> 01:09:20,010
The monks are getting help from the north.

826
01:09:20,596 --> 01:09:21,716
Getting help?

827
01:09:22,104 --> 01:09:23,514
Abolitionists.

828
01:09:24,098 --> 01:09:27,917
And most of them are the
ones folks call Quakers.

829
01:09:28,003 --> 01:09:29,112
Lot of do-gooders.

830
01:09:29,163 --> 01:09:30,915
I seen them in Ohio.

831
01:09:31,307 --> 01:09:32,514
Even so.

832
01:09:34,306 --> 01:09:35,907
They can shoot.
- What?

833
01:09:36,195 --> 01:09:37,314
Rabbits, huh?

834
01:09:37,392 --> 01:09:39,915
They're peaceable, don't
hold with war or killing,

835
01:09:39,970 --> 01:09:41,673
but some of them will kill when it comes

836
01:09:41,724 --> 01:09:44,817
to defending something,
like right or justice.

837
01:09:44,888 --> 01:09:46,620
Right, justice, what are they?

838
01:09:46,671 --> 01:09:48,618
Words, just words, that's all.

839
01:09:48,704 --> 01:09:50,407
I'd think things over.

840
01:09:51,399 --> 01:09:53,009
An evening full of surprises.

841
01:09:53,060 --> 01:09:55,023
What's the occasion, come in.

842
01:09:55,402 --> 01:09:56,915
Read it yourself.

843
01:09:57,107 --> 01:09:58,632
What, about the
committee they're sending?

844
01:09:58,683 --> 01:09:59,724
We know that.

845
01:09:59,775 --> 01:10:01,216
You don't know nothing.

846
01:10:01,599 --> 01:10:04,317
Lincoln has won, he's gonna be president.

847
01:10:04,903 --> 01:10:06,226
This some kind of joke?

848
01:10:06,277 --> 01:10:08,802
By a slim majority, but he won.

849
01:10:08,911 --> 01:10:11,353
Well, gentlemen, now what?

850
01:10:11,407 --> 01:10:12,830
Succession, what else?

851
01:10:13,704 --> 01:10:15,733
Lincoln will keep his campaign promises

852
01:10:15,784 --> 01:10:17,536
and free the slaves.

853
01:10:17,603 --> 01:10:20,829
It'll give him five
million more supporters.

854
01:10:22,101 --> 01:10:24,710
It's going to cost us dearly, gentlemen.

855
01:10:24,765 --> 01:10:26,710
Not my slaves, Mr. Lincoln.

856
01:10:35,304 --> 01:10:37,523
Were you delighted to hear the news

857
01:10:37,796 --> 01:10:39,812
that the gentlemen brought from town?

858
01:10:39,863 --> 01:10:41,414
What news is that?

859
01:10:41,898 --> 01:10:44,410
You're not going to say
you didn't listen, are you?

860
01:10:44,504 --> 01:10:46,711
I was in the pantry getting whisky.

861
01:10:46,789 --> 01:10:48,432
I must've missed it.

862
01:10:49,406 --> 01:10:51,218
Seems they had a
couple of runaway niggers

863
01:10:51,269 --> 01:10:53,604
and they're scared to death.
- And you?

864
01:10:53,800 --> 01:10:55,308
Are you scared?

865
01:10:57,707 --> 01:11:00,323
My niggers are more afraid
of me than I am of them.

866
01:11:00,392 --> 01:11:03,103
Here, brought you a little present.

867
01:11:08,600 --> 01:11:10,522
You can at least say
thanks to me, couldn't you?

868
01:11:10,573 --> 01:11:12,116
I thank you.

869
01:11:12,397 --> 01:11:13,811
Nice necklace.

870
01:11:16,998 --> 01:11:19,421
You could even strangle somebody with it.

871
01:11:20,209 --> 01:11:22,508
And lose the $1,000 you paid for me?

872
01:11:23,209 --> 01:11:24,616
Extravagant, huh?

873
01:11:26,909 --> 01:11:28,612
But that's the way I am.

874
01:11:45,402 --> 01:11:46,504
Harris!

875
01:12:00,207 --> 01:12:02,222
Was Legree there?
- No.

876
01:12:02,800 --> 01:12:05,113
Did you see my wife and child?

877
01:12:05,703 --> 01:12:07,114
No, only your sister.

878
01:12:07,165 --> 01:12:09,414
Have you told her about
the ship we've chartered?

879
01:12:09,465 --> 01:12:11,109
It won't be able to wait for her.

880
01:12:11,207 --> 01:12:13,001
She knows, yes.

881
01:12:13,214 --> 01:12:16,113
And she knows I'll pay any
price this brute asks for her.

882
01:12:16,164 --> 01:12:18,230
I don't think money
will induce Mr. Legree

883
01:12:18,281 --> 01:12:19,799
to give up your sister.

884
01:12:20,709 --> 01:12:25,311
If I know Mr. Legree, he will all right.

885
01:12:30,709 --> 01:12:32,318
I've been waiting for you.

886
01:12:41,003 --> 01:12:42,805
He says he saw you with someone.

887
01:12:43,409 --> 01:12:44,612
Who was it?

888
01:12:45,408 --> 01:12:48,018
He says he saw him come
in but he didn't leave.

889
01:12:48,103 --> 01:12:49,604
He's lying.

890
01:12:52,100 --> 01:12:53,221
You hear her?

891
01:12:53,316 --> 01:12:54,518
You're lying!

892
01:12:54,596 --> 01:12:55,807
Get outta here.

893
01:13:05,206 --> 01:13:06,619
Give me your hand.

894
01:13:09,998 --> 01:13:11,209
Now who's the man?

895
01:13:11,271 --> 01:13:13,084
Where'd you hide him?
- What man?

896
01:13:13,146 --> 01:13:15,303
Is he here, in my house?
Answer me!

897
01:13:15,506 --> 01:13:17,248
Oh, my arm, you're breaking it.

898
01:13:17,299 --> 01:13:19,404
I'll break your neck
if you don't answer.

899
01:13:19,896 --> 01:13:21,638
Up in...
- Where is he?

900
01:13:21,689 --> 01:13:24,115
Up in the barn in the attic.

901
01:13:41,203 --> 01:13:42,997
Keep an eye on her, Sambo.

902
01:13:43,102 --> 01:13:44,406
Yes, boss.

903
01:15:32,408 --> 01:15:34,009
Where are you at, boss?

904
01:15:34,603 --> 01:15:35,807
I'm coming.

905
01:15:56,902 --> 01:15:59,409
Some of the boards are rotten up there.

906
01:15:59,503 --> 01:16:01,511
They better be replaced.

907
01:16:01,620 --> 01:16:03,199
Sambo, see to it.

908
01:16:04,409 --> 01:16:07,026
Why do you look so concerned?
Nothing happened, you see.

909
01:16:07,104 --> 01:16:08,807
A miss is as good as a mile.

910
01:16:08,909 --> 01:16:12,622
I must say, that is quite a trick.

911
01:16:15,501 --> 01:16:17,016
Black witch!

912
01:16:17,206 --> 01:16:19,516
You really wanted to do me in, didn't you?

913
01:16:19,696 --> 01:16:21,907
I'm sorry I couldn't oblige.

914
01:16:23,206 --> 01:16:26,120
From now on, you're gonna be
out in the fields, working.

915
01:16:26,198 --> 01:16:27,878
Sambo, do you hear?

916
01:16:27,948 --> 01:16:30,612
Tomorrow morning, put
her to work in the fields

917
01:16:30,675 --> 01:16:32,909
in that dress she's wearing now.

918
01:16:32,972 --> 01:16:34,611
Bunk her with the others.

919
01:18:02,597 --> 01:18:04,511
Basil.
- Evening, sir.

920
01:18:06,597 --> 01:18:08,308
Well, you been thinking?

921
01:18:10,601 --> 01:18:13,501
Don't you think it's better
with me, in my house?

922
01:18:44,899 --> 01:18:46,513
Casey!

923
01:18:47,395 --> 01:18:48,513
Move!

924
01:18:50,106 --> 01:18:51,212
Tom!

925
01:19:02,096 --> 01:19:03,615
There's a saying

926
01:19:04,503 --> 01:19:06,409
I remember hearing once.

927
01:19:07,010 --> 01:19:08,315
I never...

928
01:19:08,909 --> 01:19:11,815
understood it before.

929
01:19:13,105 --> 01:19:16,715
It's very, very important.
- Don't try to speak, Uncle Tom.

930
01:19:17,402 --> 01:19:19,215
I must tell you, Casey.

931
01:19:21,488 --> 01:19:22,809
I must tell you.

932
01:19:23,309 --> 01:19:26,297
I haven't very

933
01:19:28,398 --> 01:19:29,811
much longer.

934
01:19:31,898 --> 01:19:35,305
The saying is, God helps those

935
01:19:36,691 --> 01:19:39,418
who help themselves.

936
01:19:40,703 --> 01:19:43,907
Only one thing wrong, that's
a saying for white people.

937
01:19:43,992 --> 01:19:45,102
No.

938
01:19:50,296 --> 01:19:51,615
Listen to me,

939
01:19:52,201 --> 01:19:55,597
God sees black and white the same.

940
01:19:55,807 --> 01:19:57,315
He will help you.

941
01:19:57,503 --> 01:19:59,524
You must run away.

942
01:20:01,104 --> 01:20:02,112
Yeah?

943
01:20:07,396 --> 01:20:08,709
Mr. Legree?

944
01:20:08,904 --> 01:20:11,031
Yeah, I'm Legree, but who are you?

945
01:20:11,303 --> 01:20:12,616
You don't remember me?

946
01:20:12,667 --> 01:20:14,014
I'm sorry, no.

947
01:20:14,813 --> 01:20:16,826
I owe you some money, Mr. Legree.

948
01:20:17,109 --> 01:20:18,311
A debt?

949
01:20:18,600 --> 01:20:20,211
Come in, excuse us.

950
01:20:21,309 --> 01:20:22,721
What debt?

951
01:20:23,002 --> 01:20:25,112
It concerns my sister, Casey.

952
01:20:25,717 --> 01:20:28,205
You took her from Mr.
Morrison in my place,

953
01:20:28,287 --> 01:20:32,307
and my little son Harry, who you
forced Mr. Shelby to sell to you.

954
01:20:33,510 --> 01:20:35,135
You've changed a bit since then.

955
01:20:35,186 --> 01:20:37,209
Nobody would recognize you.
What do you want?

956
01:20:37,260 --> 01:20:39,459
I invented a machine
that does in one day

957
01:20:39,523 --> 01:20:41,256
what 1,000 slaves do in a week,

958
01:20:41,307 --> 01:20:43,412
and it does it much better,

959
01:20:43,506 --> 01:20:45,820
and I bought my freedom from Mr. Morrison.

960
01:20:45,873 --> 01:20:48,350
Mr. Wilson paid me a lot
for my invention. I'm rich.

961
01:20:48,404 --> 01:20:50,908
As well as free now, Mr. Legree.

962
01:20:51,393 --> 01:20:52,615
Very interesting.

963
01:20:52,709 --> 01:20:54,717
Then you're free to get outta here.
Go on.

964
01:20:55,001 --> 01:20:56,318
Name the price

965
01:20:56,404 --> 01:20:58,318
for my child and my sister.

966
01:20:58,369 --> 01:21:00,920
I haven't got the boy
and Casey's not for sale.

967
01:21:00,990 --> 01:21:04,115
If you haven't got the
child, so much the better.

968
01:21:04,910 --> 01:21:07,299
I'll pay you whatever
you ask for him anyway,

969
01:21:07,394 --> 01:21:08,807
and for Casey.

970
01:21:08,908 --> 01:21:10,213
She wants to stay with me.

971
01:21:10,264 --> 01:21:11,705
I'll not give her up.

972
01:21:12,002 --> 01:21:15,016
You don't even believe
that yourself, Legree.

973
01:21:15,067 --> 01:21:16,643
Mr. Legree, Harris.

974
01:21:16,694 --> 01:21:19,534
I'm busy, get out.
- You listen to me, Mr. Legree!

975
01:21:19,585 --> 01:21:21,100
If I don't get...
- Just a minute, please.

976
01:21:21,151 --> 01:21:24,307
I'm sure we can discuss this
matter without violence.

977
01:21:24,377 --> 01:21:26,916
I'm willing to be reasonable about this,

978
01:21:26,971 --> 01:21:29,117
and I need more cash right now.

979
01:21:29,168 --> 01:21:31,825
We can talk this thing
over like gentlemen should.

980
01:21:32,412 --> 01:21:34,807
Who's the one let this
fancy nigger in here?

981
01:21:35,096 --> 01:21:36,299
Carl, Henry.

982
01:21:39,703 --> 01:21:42,703
Get outta here.
- Let go of me!

983
01:21:43,406 --> 01:21:45,422
Come on, get outta here.

984
01:21:51,504 --> 01:21:53,215
Here's your hat!

985
01:21:59,704 --> 01:22:03,398
No, sir, I don't want
any fancy, play niggers

986
01:22:03,454 --> 01:22:05,813
strutting around any place where I come.

987
01:22:05,868 --> 01:22:07,579
We keep them in their
place and their place

988
01:22:07,630 --> 01:22:09,612
ain't in here with decent folks.

989
01:22:09,681 --> 01:22:12,632
And just who are you to
decide who comes in here?

990
01:22:13,006 --> 01:22:14,806
I belong here and they don't,

991
01:22:15,001 --> 01:22:17,094
and that's why...
- Are you better than they are?

992
01:22:17,399 --> 01:22:20,413
Better than they are, and
better than any white nigger.

993
01:22:36,999 --> 01:22:38,346
Stop, hold it!

994
01:22:38,397 --> 01:22:41,405
My niggers are running
away, could be yours next!

995
01:22:41,468 --> 01:22:42,811
This concerns us all.

996
01:22:42,866 --> 01:22:44,804
I count on everybody to help.

997
01:23:37,502 --> 01:23:40,627
Come, Eliza, we have to get Uncle Tom.
Come.

998
01:23:50,502 --> 01:23:51,604
Uncle Tom?

999
01:23:53,003 --> 01:23:54,414
Come, Uncle Tom.

1000
01:23:56,508 --> 01:23:57,917
Hold on to me.

1001
01:23:58,096 --> 01:24:00,628
We have a long road ahead of us.

1002
01:24:01,799 --> 01:24:02,901
No.

1003
01:24:03,409 --> 01:24:07,107
I'm going on a different road.

1004
01:24:08,302 --> 01:24:11,726
My road is a long one,

1005
01:24:14,698 --> 01:24:16,698
and I must go all the way

1006
01:24:17,698 --> 01:24:19,534
by myself.

1007
01:24:22,002 --> 01:24:25,510
At the end, I'll be free.

1008
01:24:25,698 --> 01:24:28,416
And now you must go, Casey, go.

1009
01:24:32,500 --> 01:24:34,117
Goodbye, Uncle Tom.

1010
01:24:37,708 --> 01:24:39,817
Come on!
- Hurry up!

1011
01:24:44,009 --> 01:24:45,712
Hurry up, get over there!

1012
01:24:48,489 --> 01:24:49,897
Push it, push it!

1013
01:24:52,103 --> 01:24:53,109
That's it.

1014
01:25:16,890 --> 01:25:18,008
Come on!

1015
01:25:45,407 --> 01:25:47,118
Open the gates.

1016
01:25:47,296 --> 01:25:49,219
Help me, please.

1017
01:25:50,000 --> 01:25:51,024
Thank you.

1018
01:25:51,204 --> 01:25:53,424
Hurry, they have wounded.

1019
01:25:53,602 --> 01:25:54,609
Quickly.

1020
01:25:54,692 --> 01:25:56,215
Get them inside.

1021
01:25:58,195 --> 01:25:59,521
Gently.

1022
01:25:59,601 --> 01:26:01,078
You have to go right now.

1023
01:26:01,129 --> 01:26:03,109
And your family, what about them?

1024
01:26:04,709 --> 01:26:07,920
You'll have to go without
them if they're not here.

1025
01:26:08,201 --> 01:26:10,014
These men can't wait.

1026
01:26:10,097 --> 01:26:11,418
The ship...

1027
01:26:12,209 --> 01:26:13,509
is ready.

1028
01:26:18,188 --> 01:26:20,315
Boss, this way.

1029
01:26:20,498 --> 01:26:21,712
They've been spotted.

1030
01:26:21,798 --> 01:26:22,915
Come on, let's go.

1031
01:26:23,009 --> 01:26:23,821
You sure?

1032
01:26:23,872 --> 01:26:25,962
Yes sir, Casey and
another woman on the road.

1033
01:26:26,013 --> 01:26:27,286
Casey?
- Yes, sir.

1034
01:26:27,337 --> 01:26:29,310
Which way they going?
- Over toward the monastery.

1035
01:26:29,361 --> 01:26:31,325
That where the others are heading, too.

1036
01:26:31,376 --> 01:26:34,211
Come on, let's go.
I think those brothers need a lesson.

1037
01:26:46,101 --> 01:26:47,812
Faster, faster!

1038
01:26:50,698 --> 01:26:52,011
They're closer.

1039
01:26:58,700 --> 01:26:59,825
We're gaining on them!

1040
01:26:59,897 --> 01:27:00,911
Faster!

1041
01:27:07,300 --> 01:27:09,226
Eliza, Casey!

1042
01:27:09,277 --> 01:27:10,316
Eliza!

1043
01:27:11,594 --> 01:27:13,123
Is the boy all right?

1044
01:27:13,174 --> 01:27:14,917
Casey, take him, please.
- Sure.

1045
01:27:14,968 --> 01:27:17,315
It's all right, honey,

1046
01:27:22,404 --> 01:27:23,998
You'll be all right, my darling.

1047
01:27:24,099 --> 01:27:25,126
You're safe now.

1048
01:27:25,177 --> 01:27:26,817
You better hurry.
They're nearly on us

1049
01:27:26,868 --> 01:27:28,223
Close the gates.

1050
01:27:34,098 --> 01:27:35,718
No one can harm you here.

1051
01:27:36,603 --> 01:27:38,397
You'll be all right now.

1052
01:27:38,610 --> 01:27:39,931
You're safe.

1053
01:27:40,998 --> 01:27:42,100
All of you.

1054
01:27:42,175 --> 01:27:46,506
And my son, my son, he's
gonna be free, Eliza!

1055
01:27:46,592 --> 01:27:48,201
He'll be free!

1056
01:27:56,999 --> 01:27:58,709
They've run to ground.

1057
01:27:58,897 --> 01:28:01,217
Let's smoke them out like varmints.

1058
01:28:01,268 --> 01:28:02,710
What about it, boss?

1059
01:28:02,897 --> 01:28:05,014
Yeah, go ahead.
- Yes, sir.

1060
01:28:05,803 --> 01:28:09,109
Let's go!
- We'll get them outta there!

1061
01:28:10,500 --> 01:28:12,506
Stay here.
- I'm coming, too.

1062
01:28:15,301 --> 01:28:17,121
Come then.
- All right, darling.

1063
01:28:17,309 --> 01:28:19,117
There's gonna be fireworks!
- Here you are.

1064
01:28:19,168 --> 01:28:20,676
Come on, I'll cook them there.

1065
01:28:20,727 --> 01:28:22,223
You said it, let's go.

1066
01:28:51,002 --> 01:28:54,017
Casey, oh, Casey.

1067
01:30:02,692 --> 01:30:04,715
Let's hope they
honor this white flag.

1068
01:30:04,766 --> 01:30:06,606
Have you thought it
over carefully, my son?

1069
01:30:06,657 --> 01:30:09,723
Sometimes a person can think things
over so long, they never get done.

1070
01:30:09,774 --> 01:30:11,614
Pray for me, Father.
- Bless you, my son.

1071
01:30:11,665 --> 01:30:13,220
Open the gate.

1072
01:30:21,203 --> 01:30:22,521
A message!

1073
01:30:25,204 --> 01:30:26,712
I have a message.

1074
01:30:28,001 --> 01:30:29,618
I have a message for the planters.

1075
01:30:29,669 --> 01:30:32,314
Give the slaves back to us.
- And your cotton?

1076
01:30:32,400 --> 01:30:34,212
Your beautiful cotton, my son.

1077
01:30:34,275 --> 01:30:37,317
Are you aware that they
opened the levees as they ran?

1078
01:30:37,368 --> 01:30:39,325
You really ought to see to your fields.

1079
01:30:39,376 --> 01:30:40,685
And you really ought not to lie.

1080
01:30:40,736 --> 01:30:41,806
Legree!

1081
01:30:41,868 --> 01:30:43,790
They're drowning our cotton fields.

1082
01:30:43,841 --> 01:30:45,510
The sluice gates are open.

1083
01:30:45,997 --> 01:30:47,724
We're coming back later.

1084
01:30:47,896 --> 01:30:49,724
Let's go, to the field!

1085
01:30:49,802 --> 01:30:51,311
We'll still be here.

1086
01:30:51,381 --> 01:30:52,912
Come on, let's go.

1087
01:31:19,507 --> 01:31:21,210
Legree wants us to round up some niggers

1088
01:31:21,261 --> 01:31:22,679
that escaped and been causing trouble.

1089
01:31:22,730 --> 01:31:23,692
What kind of trouble?

1090
01:31:23,759 --> 01:31:25,648
Opening levees and ruining crops,

1091
01:31:25,707 --> 01:31:26,812
killing and everything.

1092
01:31:26,863 --> 01:31:28,011
Let's go!

1093
01:31:29,104 --> 01:31:30,206
Come on!

1094
01:31:48,902 --> 01:31:51,719
The gates, the sluice gates!

1095
01:31:52,207 --> 01:31:54,522
Come on, close the sluice gates!

1096
01:32:37,010 --> 01:32:39,325
There's one of them still here.

1097
01:32:44,108 --> 01:32:45,213
There.

1098
01:32:46,807 --> 01:32:49,824
You, damn you, you were their leader,

1099
01:32:49,901 --> 01:32:51,651
the one who caused me all this trouble.

1100
01:32:51,702 --> 01:32:53,307
Leave him alone, Legree.

1101
01:32:59,899 --> 01:33:02,306
How much do you want for him, Legree?

1102
01:33:09,005 --> 01:33:11,027
Dead niggers cost nothing.

1103
01:33:23,209 --> 01:33:24,420
Uncle Tom.

1104
01:33:28,900 --> 01:33:30,205
Uncle Tom.

1105
01:33:32,504 --> 01:33:34,121
Thank you

1106
01:33:34,496 --> 01:33:38,033
for coming, Master George.

1107
01:33:41,209 --> 01:33:43,523
I knew you would

1108
01:33:45,601 --> 01:33:47,609
some day.

1109
01:33:48,618 --> 01:33:49,718
You...

1110
01:34:14,410 --> 01:34:16,263
You sure you seen something?

1111
01:34:16,340 --> 01:34:18,582
I seen something, and it was black.

1112
01:34:18,633 --> 01:34:21,116
Well, I ain't seen nothing.
Let's go.

1113
01:36:28,109 --> 01:36:31,317
Now y'all gonna get a
taste of black justice.

1114
01:36:32,112 --> 01:36:34,227
You been making slaves out of us,

1115
01:36:34,398 --> 01:36:36,203
you been hunting us down,

1116
01:36:36,702 --> 01:36:38,605
you been raping our women,

1117
01:36:40,008 --> 01:36:41,819
you been taking our respect.

1118
01:36:43,603 --> 01:36:47,407
May God damn you to hell for
what you did to my daughter.

1119
01:36:48,996 --> 01:36:50,020
No!
